10 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 905 of Title 40, unless there is
12 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 A. Pursuant to the provisions of Section 904 of Title 40 of the
14 Oklahoma Statutes, the Oklahoma Workforce Commission shall implement
15 programs in this state to address the following:
16 1. Development of a workforce in high demand occupations or
17 critical occupations as determined by the Oklahoma Workforce
18 Commission. Actions taken by the Commission may include:
19 a. identifying the needs of higher education institutions
20 suited for certain high demand or critical workforce
21 areas and helping the institutions develop and
22 implement plans to address those needs,
23 b. identify outcomes based on funding,
24
