1 c. identifying and partnering for scholarship match
2 opportunities for students interested in these high
3 demand and critical workforce fields, and
4 d. helping institutions increase program capacity;
5 2. Development of work-based learning opportunities, which may
6 include, but not be limited to, internships, apprenticeships, and
7 other career exploration and exposure; and
8 3. Development of innovation within public schools as defined
9 in Section 1-106 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes that supports
10 workforce success, which may include:
11 a. developing enhanced or unique education pathways,
12 b. utilizing development grants for basic skills
13 development,
14 c. utilizing regulatory innovation grants, and
15 d. assisting in the development of career-connected high
16 schools.
17 B. The Commission may administer these programs through funds
18 in the Oklahoma Workforce Commission Revolving Fund created in
19 Section 3 of this act.
20 C. The Commission shall promulgate rules necessary to implement
21 the provisions of this section.
22 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
